<p><a href="https://wellows.com/blog/google-ai-overviews-ranking-factors/">96% of AI Overview citations</a> come from sources with strong E-E-A-T signals. Pages with 15 or more recognized entities show 4.8 times higher selection probability.</p>
<p>The reward for getting cited is significant. Cited pages earn <a href="https://www.dataslayer.ai/blog/google-ai-overviews-the-end-of-traditional-ctr-and-how-to-adapt-in-2025">35% more organic clicks</a> than non-cited competitors. In a world where AI Overviews reduce overall CTR by 61%, being one of the cited sources is the difference between getting traffic and getting nothing.</p>
<p>For a deeper dive on the broader topic, see our <a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">generative engine optimization guide</a>.</p>
